               <msContents>
                  <summary>Originally compiled in Arabic by <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f502">Aḥmad Ibn ‘Abdullāh</persName>, translated into Persian by more than one translator. The present manuscript contains the original Arabic with a Persian paraphrase or as described in the author’s preface, the Persian translation, divided into forty chapters, each chapter containing ten traditions: لباب الخبار که چهل بابست و در هر باب ده حدیث در نظر آورده این گنه کار بفارسی ترجمه کرده از برای مبتدیان و کسانی که بر عربی اطلاع ندارند...However, chapter 3 contains eleven traditions, while chapters 19 and 38 have nine traditions each, and there is a confusion in the sequence of the headings in chapter 12.</summary>
